Description: Part of a wooden coffin; paint on plaster; three rows of blue Hieroglyphic text and two similar columns. Joins EA46656 according to Zitman (2010, 129).
Excavator/field collector: Excavated by: Dr David George Hogarth
Bibliographic references: Zitman 2010 / The necropolis of Assiut: a case study of local Egyptian funerary culture from the Old Kingdom to the end of the Middle Kingdom (II, 128, 215)
